{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "SurfaceLayerProfile",
        "description": "Monin-Obukhov surface-layer similarity theory for the atmospheric surface layer, from Seinfeld & Pandis (2006) \"Atmospheric Chemistry and Physics\", 2nd ed., Chapter 16 \"Meteorology of the Local Scale\". Observed-only algebraic component: from the friction velocity u_star, surface sensible heat flux q_z, and surface-layer geometry it computes the Monin-Obukhov length L (Eq. 16.70), the dimensionless stability parameter ζ = z/L, the Businger-Dyer stability functions φ_m and φ_h (Eq. 16.75), their integrated forms ψ_m and ψ_h (Eq. 16.78-16.79), and the stability-corrected mean wind speed ū (Eq. 16.66 with the Eq. 16.77 correction). Migrated from AtmosphericDynamics.jl@816cc391 src/local_scale_meteorology.jl:107 (`SurfaceLayerProfile` @component); the 4 upstream @constants (g, κ, ĉ_p, ε_q) are declared as fixed-default parameters.",
        "tags": [
            "atmospheric_dynamics",
            "seinfeld-pandis",
            "boundary-layer",
            "monin-obukhov",
            "observed-only",
            "ch16"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-17T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "AtmosphericDynamics.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (esm-3dve)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Seinfeld, J. H., & Pandis, S. N. (2006). Atmospheric Chemistry and Physics: From Air Pollution to Climate Change, 2nd ed. Wiley. Chapter 16 (Meteorology of the Local Scale), pp. 720-760 — Eq. 16.66 (logarithmic wind profile), Eq. 16.70 (Monin-Obukhov length), Eq. 16.75 (Businger-Dyer stability functions), Eq. 16.78-16.79 (integrated stability functions). ISBN 978-0-471-72018-8."
            },
            {
                "citation": "Businger, J. A., Wyngaard, J. C., Izumi, Y., & Bradley, E. F. (1971). Flux-Profile Relationships in the Atmospheric Surface Layer. Journal of the Atmospheric Sciences, 28(2), 181-189. DOI 10.1175/1520-0469(1971)028<0181:FPRITA>2.0.CO;2."
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "SurfaceLayerProfile": {
            "reference": {
                "notes": "source_ref: AtmosphericDynamics.jl@816cc391:src/local_scale_meteorology.jl:107\nUpstream `SurfaceLayerProfile` is a ModelingToolkit `@component` implementing Monin-Obukhov similarity theory for the atmospheric surface layer. g, κ, ĉ_p, ε_q are upstream `@constants`; z, z₀, T₀, ρ, u_star, q_z are `@parameters`; L, ζ, φ_m, φ_h, ψ_m, ψ_h, ū are `@variables` bound by 7 algebraic equations (no time derivative). For standalone serialization the 4 `@constants` are declared as fixed-default parameters here, matching the sibling scale_height.esm. The 7 equations are unchanged from upstream; `mtk2esm` reorders commutative `*`/`+` operands, rewrites `x^(-n)` as `1/x^n`, and folds `((1-15ζ)^0.25)^2` to `(1-15ζ)^0.5` (algebraically identical). The `π/2` term of the ψ_m unstable branch is folded to the float literal 1.5707963267948966.\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1e-6): observed-only algebraic system (no ODE integration); rel=1e-6 covers float64 roundoff and cross-runner libm differences in the `^`/`log`/`atan` chain. Near-zero outputs in the neutral regime (ζ, ψ_m, ψ_h ~ 1e-8..1e-13, where π/2 − 2·atan(x≈1) cancels) carry a per-assertion abs=1e-6 — already far tighter than the upstream test suite's atol=1e-4 for ζ."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1e-06
            },
            "variables": {
                "z": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 10.0,
                    "description": "Height above ground"
                },
                "z₀": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 0.1,
                    "description": "Roughness length (Table 16.1)"
                },
                "T₀": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 288.15,
                    "description": "Reference temperature (surface)"
                },
                "ρ": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/m^3",
                    "default": 1.225,
                    "description": "Air density"
                },
                "u_star": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m/s",
                    "default": 0.3,
                    "description": "Friction velocity"
                },
                "q_z": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "W/m^2",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Surface sensible heat flux (positive upward)"
                },
                "g": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m/s^2",
                    "default": 9.807,
                    "description": "Gravitational acceleration"
                },
                "κ": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.4,
                    "description": "von Karman constant (dimensionless)"
                },
                "ĉ_p": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "J/(kg*K)",
                    "default": 1005.0,
                    "description": "Specific heat of air at constant pressure"
                },
                "ε_q": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "W/m^2",
                    "default": 1e-10,
                    "description": "Small regularization for heat flux"
                },
                "L": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m",
                    "description": "Monin-Obukhov length (Eq. 16.70)"
                },
                "ζ": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Stability parameter z/L (dimensionless)"
                },
                "φ_m": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Momentum stability function (Eq. 16.75) (dimensionless)"
                },
                "φ_h": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Heat stability function (Eq. 16.75) (dimensionless)"
                },
                "ψ_m": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Integrated momentum stability function (dimensionless)"
                },
                "ψ_h": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Integrated heat stability function (dimensionless)"
                },
                "ū": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m/s",
                    "description": "Mean wind speed at height z (Eq. 16.66 with stability)"
                }
            },
            "equations": [
                {
                    "lhs": "L",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    -1,
